# Sanity CMS API Test Endpoints
# Use with VS Code REST Client extension or similar

### Get all blog posts
GET http://localhost:5000/api/blog
Content-Type: application/json

### Get featured blog posts
GET http://localhost:5000/api/blog/featured
Content-Type: application/json

### Get blog post by ID
GET http://localhost:5000/api/blog/1
Content-Type: application/json

### Get blog post by slug
GET http://localhost:5000/api/blog/slug/test-post
Content-Type: application/json

### Create new blog post
POST http://localhost:5000/api/blog
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Post from Sanity",
  "slug": "test-post-sanity",
  "content": "This is a test post content created through the Sanity CMS API.",
  "excerpt": "A test post for Sanity CMS integration.",
  "authorName": "Test Author",
  "category": "Test",
  "readTime": 2,
  "tags": ["test", "sanity", "cms"],
  "featured": true
}

### Update blog post
PATCH http://localhost:5000/api/blog/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Updated Test Post",
  "content": "This content has been updated through the Sanity CMS API."
}

### Delete blog post
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/blog/1
Content-Type: application/json